snippet.title: Ashville
snippet.description:
Ashville Aggregates offer waste management service to the entire construction industry. Our roots within the construction industry mean we have the expertise and know-how to provide Waste Disposal and Transportation Service (also know as haulage) which is second to none.

We are best known for our fleet of 8×4 and 4×2 grab lorries offering grab hire and aggregates supply in London and surround areas. Our fleet of 8×4 tippers provides tipper hire for muck away and aggregate supply services.

Skip Hire is a fabulous alternative to the grab and tipper lorries we offer. Within London, Grab Hire is not always logistically possible. Our 8-yard skips are perfect for general waste and excavation projects. Skip Hire can exchange a skip multiple times in a day or we offer a wait and load service.

We are an Aggregates Supplier offering both primary and recycled aggregates. We can supply between 5 tonnes to 20 tonnes per visit and can provide muck away simultaneously.

youtube.com/thisisashville

Which is all a myth.
As there is already everything, and this is already unmissable, to already No One.

snippet.title: Temple of the Way of Light
snippet.description:
The Temple of the Way of Light is a pioneering ayahuasca retreat center in the Peruvian Amazon that has facilitated safe ayahuasca retreats for thousands of guests from more than 30 countries since  March 2007. 

Offering a synthesis of ancient Shipibo healing traditions and modern and Eastern integrative practices, the Temple is proud to be known as the safest and one of the most respected and long-established retreat centers in the Amazon Rainforest.

All ayahuasca healing retreats feature a balance of highly experienced female and male healers (Onanya) from the indigenous Shipibo tribe. Our team of healers represents over 250 years of experience practicing the ancient art of ayahuasca shamanism. They are supported by our highly trained and experienced Western facilitators, who act as a critical cultural bridge between the healers and our guests.

snippet.title: Hamster Productions
snippet.description:
LEGO Stop Motion | Science Documentaries

Welcome to the official Hamster Productions YouTube channel! 🎩 
Here you can watch all my LEGO stop-motion films, science documentaries, and more 📽

Please subscribe - it is free and will alert you when I make a new film! 🚨

FAQ:

Q: What camera do you use?
A: I have used many different cameras over the years. I currently use a Cannon 550D DSLR camera, which provides great quality, but needs a powerful computer to edit. Before this I used a Logitech 9000 webcam for many years, a great little camera that does the job. 

Q: What software do you use?
A: I currently use DragonFrame for animation and Davinci Resolve for post-production. I also use Photoshop for frame-by-frame "special effects". Before this I used the free Windows video editing software, so I recommend trying that first!

Q: When's your next film coming out?
A: Follow my social media pages (linked below) to see the progress on my latest production!

snippet.title: RexTV
snippet.description:
RexTV is a new media enterprise dedicated to ensuring that views often excluded from the mainstream media are aired and heard. Rex's guests come from the arenas of politics, business, academia, science, and the arts. 

Rex Murphy is a regular columnist for The National Post, a former CBC TV commentator, and was the host of the popular CBC Radio One's  "Cross Country Check Up" for 21 years. Born and raised in Newfoundland, he entered Memorial University of Newfoundland at age 15 and graduated three years later with a scholarship to attend the University of Oxford as a Rhodes Scholar. He has published two books, "Canada and Other Matters of Opinion" and "Points of View". His acclaimed 1994 documentary film "Unpeopled Shores", about the collapse of Newfoundland's fisheries, resonated across Canada and beyond. His longtime producer at The National, Tony Burman, summed it up well: "Very few Canadians turn off the set when Rex Murphy is on."
